\par CATCHWORDS: 
\par VOLUNTARY ASSOCIATIONS - Declaration and injunction sought requiring calling of meeting pursuant to requisition of member - Organisations \endash  whether preconditions satisfied - whether requests to call meeting validly made - whether request via email 
\'93in writing\'94 - held that requests validly made \endash  held that email is writing \endash  whether dispute justiciable - whether constitution of organisation constitutes a legally binding and enforceable contract \endash 
 where Constitution had been treated by parties as binding in earlier litigation \endash held that organisation\rquote s constitution is legally binding and enforceable \endash  whether relief should be refused on discretionary grounds  
