Cameron v Hogan}{\f0\fs20\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033  is not out of touch with the times. The case ran for five days before Commission
er Odes, involved another action which had to be settled, involved three interlocutory injunction applications and then this appeal to the Court of Appeal. The dispute has involved the time of seven Judges. There has been an absurd amount of time, money a
